snippet.textDisplay:
What is Eid e Ghadeer?? about this Hadees s.a.w.w. (Mann Kunto Moula Fa,haaza Ali un Moula)
Prophet Muhammad Mustafa (s.a.w.w) on his way back from His last Hajj pilgrimage, Message came from ALLAH which is also mentioned in the Quran
In this place, the following verse of the Qur'an was revealed:
"O Apostle! Deliver what has been sent down to you from your Lord; and if you don't do it, you have not delivered His message (at all); and Allah will protect you from the people ..." Surah al Maida (Qur'an 5:67) 
Then The Prophet [s.a.w.w] held up the hand of 'Ali and said: 
"Mann Kunto Moula, Fa'haaza Ali un Moula"
"For whoever I am his Leader (Moula), 'Ali is his Leader (Moula)."
"O' God, love those who love him, and be hostile to those who are hostile to him"
Immediately after the Prophet [s.a.w.w] finished his speech, the following verse of the Qur'an was revealed:
"Today I have perfected your religion and completed my favour upon you, and I was satisfied that Islam be your religion." (Qur'an Surah al Maidah)

snippet.textDisplay: When I first listened to this song, I was blown away. Since then I haven't been able to get it out my head.  This song is the way it is both because of Javed Bashir AND Ali Azmat. Ali Azmat's singing is as intense in the parts that he sings but Javed Bashir carried this song in such a way that you have to give him more credit. But to the people who are complaining about the production and how every instrument has been squeezed in don't know the firs thing about music. This is Coke Studio and this is where the folk qawal meets fusion.The song is almost 10 minutes and it's not like the intensity grows right away. It starts simple and then grows and grows and takes you to places. It gets intense in the last 3 minutes and it wouldn't have felt this way if those instruments weren't used. I think this is one of the best songs of this season and it fits in the modern age perfectly the way its produced. Hats off to you Jaffer Zaidi!
